  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOB SCOPE:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage end-to-end recruitment from sourcing to onboarding administration and ensuring timely coordination.</li><li>Coordinate interview scheduling and participate in interviews as the HR representative to assess candidate suitability and ensure fair and consistent hiring practices</li><li>Prepare and administer employment documentation, including appointment letters, contracts, and required regulatory or statutory clearances</li><li>Oversee training administration, including course coordination, maintenance of training records, funding or grant claims, and compliance tracking</li><li>Serve as a reliable HR point of contact for employee lifecycle matters such as probation tracking, contract renewals, and general HR enquiries</li><li>Administer staff engagement initiatives and internal communications, ensuring activities are well coordinated and properly documented</li><li>Maintain accurate and timely HR records, data, and reports in accordance with organisational policies and statutory requirements</li><li>Ensure HR processes and records are well-documented, consistently implemented, accurate and timely filing, and HR system updates.</li><li>Assist with any ad-hoc duty as assigned.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENT:</strong></p><ul><li>Team Player, positive and collaborative energy most crucial</li><li>Minimally a Diploma in Human Resources or a related field.</li><li>Proven HR experience with minimum of 2 years, preferably in F&B, Retail, or Hospitality industries.</li><li>Experience with HRMS, ideally Info-tech</li><li>Fluent in basic Excel, Word, GoogleSheet skills</li><li>Familiar with Singapore Employment Law or MOM Policies, including but not limited to Employment Act</li><li>Detail-oriented and able to work independently with minimum amount of supervision</li><li>Good written & communication skills.</li><li>Ability to thrive in a fast-paced work environment.</li></ul>",
